<subSubSection id="C31343D2FFC9FFAC6180FA1CC7DFF9A8" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB61059FFC9FFAC6180FA1CC7DFF9A8" blockId="5.[151,1436,1374,1581]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">
<emphasis id="B97DCC4BFFC9FFAC6180FA1CC460FA61" bold="true" box="[199,315,1482,1508]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is a member of ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C096BDAFFC9FFAC63D3FA1CC6FCFA61" authorityName="" authorityYear="1889" baseAuthorityName="Hodge" baseAuthorityYear="1863" box="[660,935,1482,1508]" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Copidognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oculatus">
<emphasis id="B97DCC4BFFC9FFAC63D3FA1CC6FCFA61" box="[660,935,1482,1508]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">Copidognathus oculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group’ (
<bibRefCitation id="EF986DA8FFC9FFAC654FFA1CC1EAFA61" author="Bartsch, I." box="[1032,1201,1482,1508]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" pagination="299 - 321" refId="ref8911" refString="Bartsch, I. (1999 c) Copidognathus (Halacaridae: Acari) from Western Australia: five species of the oculatus group. Records of the Western Australian Museum, 19, 299 - 321." type="journal article" year="1999">Bartsch 1999c</bibRefCitation>
). This species is one of the small-sized members of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C096BDAFFC9FFAC6359FA38C726F98D" authorityName="" authorityYear="1889" baseAuthorityName="Hodge" baseAuthorityYear="1863" box="[542,637,1518,1544]" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Copidognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oculatus">
<emphasis id="B97DCC4BFFC9FFAC6359FA38C726F98D" box="[542,637,1518,1544]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">oculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. Idiosoma 175-185 μm long. Posterior porose areola on anterior dorsal plate bow-shaped, with rosette pores.
</paragraph>
